Package cs131.pa1.filter.sequential

Class SequentialFilter

java.lang.Object
cs131.pa1.filter.Filter
cs131.pa1.filter.sequential.SequentialFilter
Direct Known Subclasses:
CatFilter, ChangeDirectoryFilter, ExitFilter, GrepFilter, HeadFilter, ListFilter, PrintFilter, RedirectFilter, TailFilter, UniqFilter, WordCountFilter, WorkingDirectoryFilter
public abstract class SequentialFilter extends cs131.pa1.filter.Filter
An abstract class that extends the Filter and implements the basic functionality of all filters. Each filter should extend this class and implement functionality that is specific for this filter. You should not modify this class.
Author:
cs131a

    • processLine

      protected abstract String processLine​(String line)
      Called by the process() method for every encountered line in the input queue. It then performs the processing specific for each filter and returns the result. Each filter inheriting from this class must implement its own version of processLine() to take care of the filter-specific processing.
      Parameters:
      line - the line got from the input queue
      Returns:
      the line after the filter-specific processing
